shared_text:
Opportunities for Youth
May 28 at 10:43 PM ·

ASU Youth Voter Engagement Academy - Job Opportunity
The Pastor Center for Politics and Public Service partnering with Opportunities for Youth is looking for Outreach Ambassadors.

Outreach Ambassadors will help reach young adults in Maricopa County with information about voting and elections in Arizona. Ambassadors can earn up to $2,500* by completing training and carrying out a range of online outreach activities targeting youth ages 16-24 with a special focus on Congressional Districts 3 and 7 (much of the West Valley).
This project will run from June through mid-November.

For details/applications please visit:
https://oppforyouth.org/join-the-team

#asujobs #youthvote #jobs #asu

Phoenix Public Library
July 8, 2019 at 10:05 PM ·

July’s #justreadppl theme is Space! ✨🌙 This month, look to the stars for your reading inspiration. Whether you seek to explore space facts with an astronomy book or you instead delve into an interstellar science-fiction read, the universe is the limit! Visit our website for spacetastic recommendations.☀️📚 Read with us! Tag #justreadppl http://bit.ly/2JkN8Bq
*************************
We at Phoenix Public Library want you to maintain your goal to read for leisure and/or read for self-education. Just Read is a come-as-you-are, read-what-you-like online book club and so much more!
Each month, we will announce a book club genre or theme on our website. Read what you like within this genre or theme. Participate throughout the month by posting on social media, tagging Phoenix Public Library and #justreadppl to share, discuss and recommend your book choice. Or, follow along on your own without posting on social media – it’s all good! Follow us on Facebook, Instagram, Twitter and YouTube or visit our website for more about the Just Read online book club.
